diction is that the gBGC level minimizing the load depends only on the mutational bias and population size. These surprising results suggest that gBGC may have nonnegligible fitness consequences and could play a significant role in the evolution of genetic systems. They also shed light on the evolution of gBGC itself.},
  file = {/Users/maudgautier/Zotero/storage/CIFD6CZZ/Glémin - 2010 - Surprising Fitness Consequences of GC-Biased Gene .pdf},
